&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Community Children’s Nursing Service (CCNS)- Band 6 Deputy Team Manager &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen within the CCNS for a full time Deputy Team Manager to support the operational and professional management of the CCNS North Team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will support and assist the Team Manager to operationally manage, provide leadership, professional advice and care for the Community Children’s Service in the designated Team. The post holder will have responsibility for management of a designated caseload delegating responsibilities and tasks as required. They will undertake specialist nursing assessments and deliver care for children with complex needs in relation to continuing care, ensuring the process is followed. The post holder will be working in partnership with the appropriate multi-disciplinary agencies to provide skilled nursing care to children and young people in a variety of community settings. These include continuing care packages, special needs schools, children’s outpatients and the clinical arm of care closer to home&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be team specific but will be expected to cross cover according to service needs. They will participate in meeting the needs of the service covering 24hrs a day, 7 days per week and the on call service. In addition intergrated working to support the acure setting through the care closer to home service, admission avoidance and early discharge.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Candidates will be expected to have sufficient paediatric experience, working with children and those with complex healthcare needs in a variety of settings. Possession of a teaching qualification would be advantageous. We offer a comprehensive induction programme and you would be given the opportunity to develop your knowledge, experience and skills within a friendly and supportive environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date - 18th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information, or to arrange a visit to the team please contact Paula Browne, Team Manager on 01443 802458 / 07949 607469&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Additionally: Janelle Courtney Senior Nurse CCNS / Janelle.courtney@wales.nhs.uk/ 01633618020&lt;/p&gt;
